# Project Rules

## Technical Stack
- TypeScript (ES2022)
- Vite for bundling
- Pure CSS with BEM methodology
- No frontend frameworks (Vanilla JS only)
- pnpm for package management

## Architecture
- Modular, section-based architecture.
- Core Bundle: Loaded on every page (tokens, global components, SectionLoader).
- Page-Specific Bundles: Separate entry points per page to minimize payload.
- Sections auto-instantiate via `data-section` attributes.

## CSS Guidelines
- Follow BEM methodology (`.block__element--modifier`).
- Use CSS custom properties (design tokens) from `unified.css`.
- Keep CSS flat; avoid deep nesting.
- No CSS frameworks.

## Performance & SEO
- Maintain 100/100 Lighthouse scores.
- Proper use of semantic HTML and landmarks.
- Optimized asset loading.

## Development Workflow
- All changes must be documented in a PR.
- Use pnpm for all dependency management and scripts.
- GitHub Actions handles CI/CD and deployment to GitHub Pages.
